raw_data.title: Engineering Technician
raw_data.description: Oversees the field assembly of modular log cabin kits provided by Conestoga Log Cabins & Homes. Responsibilities include coordinating logistics, managing subcontractors, ensuring compliance with building codes and safety standards, and maintaining project schedules and budgets. The role requires interpreting technical drawings, resolving on-site issues, and serving as the primary liaison between clients, vendors, and internal teams. The Construction Project Manager ensures all work aligns with contract specifications and quality expectations. Familiarity with modular construction, site preparation, and federal reporting requirements is essential. This position may require travel to remote job sites.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Oversees the design, development, planning, coordination, and execution of log cabin kit assembly projects using Conestoga Log Cabins & Homes systems. This role ensures all construction activities comply with contract specifications, safety regulations, and quality standards. Responsibilities include managing subcontractors, monitoring project schedules and budgets, coordinating material deliveries, and resolving field issues. The Project Manager serves as the primary point of contact for clients and government representatives, ensuring clear communication and timely reporting. The ideal candidate possesses experience in modular or residential construction, strong leadership skills, and the ability to interpret technical drawings and specifications. This position may require travel to remote job sites and adherence to government-mandated reporting and documentation standards.
